notes = "(!) sega_101.bin (md5): f273555d7d91e8a5a6bfd9bcf066331c|(!) sega_100.bin (md5): 2aba43c2f1526c5e898dfe1cafbfc53a|Built on Ymir's cycle-accurate hardware layer (verbatim upstream).|Requires Saturn BIOS ROM (place in system directory).|Japanese BIOS files (Sega Saturn BIOS v1.00/v1.01 (JAP).bin) are also supported.|Note: sega1003.bin (JP v1.003) is NOT supported due to compatibility issues.|Visit https://github.com/coredds/brimir for more information."

description = "Brimir is a high-performance libretro core for Sega Saturn emulation, built on Ymir's cycle-accurate foundation. Features Mednafen-competitive rendering performance (60+ FPS @ 704x448i) through tile-row caching and SIMD optimizations. Ymir's hardware layer stays verbatim upstream — all features and enhancements are implemented in the Brimir bridge layer. Active development targets cheat support, all Saturn controller types, RetroAchievements, screen rotation, save state compression, and future JIT support. The core requires a Saturn BIOS ROM to function."
